programme.title: Evropa e Egër
programme.desc: Ep 1: Evropa Veriore, vendi ku bie dëborë gjatë pjesës më të madhe vitit dhe shtëpia e disa prej krijesave më mbresëlënëse në planet. Që nga grabitqarët më të mëdhenj që enden nëpër fushat e akullta, deri te mishngrënësit më të vegjël në tokë që rriten pyjet e ngrira. Kjo botë armiqësore e mbuluar nga bora njeh vetëm të mbijetuarit më të fortë, sepse në tokën evropiane borës dhe akullit nuk ka zgjidhje tjetër, veçse të përshtatesh ose vdesësh.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: The Next Generation
programme.sub-title: Where No One Has Gone Before
programme.desc: The Enterprise crew members find themselves thrust into the middle of a puzzling mystery after their propulsion system backfires. Sci-fi drama, starring Patrick Stewart.

programme.title: Star Trek: Voyager
programme.desc: A Kazon child hoping to reach the rank of warrior attacks a shuttle piloted by Chakotay, who unwittingly condemns his would-be enemy to death by refusing to fight back. Sci-fi adventure, starring Robert Beltran.

programme.title: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine
programme.desc: Alien delegates from the Gamma Quadrant prefer gambling in the bar to negotiation - and Quark's attempts to cheat them leave him playing a deadly game with the senior officers' lives. Starring Armin Shimerman, Avery Brooks and Nana Visitor.

programme.title: Stargate Atlantis
programme.desc: Part two of three. The Wraith close in and the future of the city looks doomed, until help arrives in the form of the Stargate SG-1 vessel Daedalus, bringing a new military contingent from Earth. Joe Flanigan stars.

programme.title: Stargate SG-1
programme.sub-title: There but for the Grace of God
programme.desc: Daniel enters an alternative reality where he witnesses the invasion of Earth by the Goa'uld. Sci-fi drama, starring Richard Dean Anderson.

programme.title: 2012: Ice Age
programme.desc: A volcanic eruption in Iceland sends a vast glacier hurtling toward America, plunging the country into an ice age. A family struggles to find a safe place to hide as conditions make survival increasingly difficult. Sci-fi thriller, starring Patrick Labyorteaux and Julie McCullough.

programme.title: Teleshopping
programme.desc: A chance for viewers to buy bargains galore at home.

programme.title: Merlin
programme.desc: The wizard has an unexpected meeting with mysterious old sorcerer Taliesin, who takes him to the crystal cave and shows him a glimpse of the future. However, the gift turns out to be more of a curse when Merlin sees Morgana preparing to kill Uther and realises he faces the dangerous task of trying to change the course of destiny. Magical adventure series, starring Colin Morgan.

programme.title: Merlin
programme.desc: Arthur is pressured to enter into an arranged marriage to Elena, a princess visiting from another kingdom. However, when Merlin learns the would-be bride has a dark secret, he sets about trying to discover what interest she could possibly have in pursuing a union with Camelot's heir. Fantasy drama, guest starring Miriam Margolyes, with Colin Morgan and Bradley James.

programme.title: Merlin
programme.desc: Gwen is forced to choose between saving the life of Arthur and her estranged brother Elyan, with one of them set to die at the hands of Cenred. She tries desperately to find a way out, but with Morgana and Morgause doing everything they can to thwart her efforts, the outcome looks bleak. Starring Angel Coulby and Emilia Fox.

programme.title: Merlin
programme.desc: Arthur embarks on a quest to prove himself a worthy heir to the throne of Camelot by retrieving the Golden Trident from the Fisher King. However, Morgana spots an opportunity to attack the prince outside the safety of the citadel, and plays a trick that leaves him in mortal peril. Starring Colin Morgan, Bradley James and Katie McGrath, with Donald Sumpter (Being Human).

programme.title: Merlin
programme.sub-title: Love in the Time of Dragons
programme.desc: Gaius is overjoyed when an old flame arrives in Camelot, but Merlin discovers she has been possessed by an evil creature. However, the physician refuses to heed his young friend's warnings, putting the king's life in peril as a result. Guest starring Pauline Collins.

programme.title: Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files
programme.desc: Destination Truth presenter Josh Gates joins the hunt for an aquatic creature in Iceland, and WWE wrestler Kofi Kingston helps investigate a Stonehenge mystery.

programme.title: Merlin's Apprentice
programme.desc: First of a two-part family-friendly fantasy, starring Sam Neill as the great wizard, who returns to Camelot to discover the Holy Grail has been stolen. With the help of a youngster named Jack (John Reardon), he vows to find the chalice and restore the city to its former glory. Also starring Miranda Richardson and Andrew Jackson.

programme.title: Merlin's Apprentice
programme.desc: Conclusion of the two-part family-friendly fantasy, starring Sam Neill as the great wizard, who returns to Camelot to discover the Holy Grail has been stolen. With the help of a youngster named Jack (John Reardon) he vows to find the chalice and restore the city to its former glory. Also starring Miranda Richardson and Andrew Jackson.

programme.title: Need for Speed
programme.desc: A street racer is betrayed by a friend, and ends up being framed for causing a death during an illegal contest. Two years later, he is released from prison and returns to the underground racing circuit with revenge in mind. Action adventure based on the video game, starring Aaron Paul, Dominic Cooper, Imogen Poots and Michael Keaton.

programme.title: Mythica: A Quest for Heroes
programme.desc: An aspiring wizard escapes from a life of servitude to pursue her dream of developing her magical powers. She gathers a band of heroes together and leads them on a mission to save her friend, who has fallen into the clutches of a monstrous ogre. Fantasy adventure, starring Melanie Stone and Kevin Sorbo.

programme.title: Avengers Grimm: Time Wars
programme.desc: When Rumpelstiltskin tries to take over Earth, the Avengers Grimm must track him through time in order to defeat him. Fantasy adventure, starring Marah Fairclough, Lauren Parkinson and Christina Licciardi.

programme.title: Tornado Warning
programme.desc: A teenager whose home was destroyed by an unusual tornado grows up to be an amateur storm chaser, and investigates when similar freak storms start occurring across the world. He enlists the aid of a meteorologist in getting to the truth, and discovers the strange weather is cover for an alien invasion. Sci-fi thriller, starring Kari Wuhrer and Jeff Fahey.

programme.title: 12 Disasters
programme.desc: A dark star appears in the sky on Christmas Eve, leaving mankind convinced the end of the world is nigh. A series of devastating natural disasters occuring all around the world seemingly validates the belief, and it falls to a small band of heroes to prevent the apocalypse. Thriller, with Ed Quinn and Magda Apanowicz.

programme.title: Teleshopping
programme.desc: A chance for viewers to buy bargains galore at home.

programme.title: Warehouse 13
programme.desc: Part one of two. A pair of secret service agents are transferred from the president's protection team to the secret unit where the collection of every supernatural and unexplained item that the US government has ever claimed is stored. Pilot episode of the sci-fi drama, starring Eddie McClintock, Joanne Kelly and Saul Rubinek.

programme.title: Warehouse 13
programme.desc: Part two of two. Secret service agents Myka and Peter ease into their roles at Warehouse 13, discovering the treasures it holds, and meet Lena, the proprietor of a B&B near the base. Sci-fi drama, starring Eddie McClintock, Joanne Kelly and Saul Rubinek.

programme.title: Warehouse 13
programme.desc: Pete and Myka are sent to Chicago to pursue bank robbers who use a song as their weapon. Meanwhile, at the warehouse, Artie investigates a breach in security. Starring Eddie McClintock and Joanne Kelly.

programme.title: Warehouse 13
programme.desc: Pete and Myka investigate a town whose inhabitants' minds are being altered, leading them to act impetuously. Meanwhile, Artie is baffled by the energy flows present in the warehouse. Sci-fi drama, starring Eddie McClintock and Joanne Kelly.

programme.title: Warehouse 13
programme.desc: Artie gets kidnapped by the source of the warehouse's security breach, Claudia Donovan, who holds him responsible for the death of her brother. Drama, starring Eddie McClintock and Allison Scagliotti.

programme.title: Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files
programme.desc: The team travels to Indiana to investigate the video of a ghost-like apparition in a war cemetery, and an unexplained event involving cattle is explored in Colorado.

programme.title: Tomb Invader
programme.desc: Several college students find clues that lead them to an ancient tomb deep in the jungle. The relics help them get closer to the truth about a missing family member. Action adventure, starring Gina Vitori, Samantha Bowling and Andrew J Katers.

programme.title: End of the World
programme.desc: A family flees from a series of natural disasters caused by a solar storm, seeking relative safety in nearby caves. Disaster movie, starring Jhey Castles.

programme.title: Kick-Ass
programme.desc: A teenage comic-book fan sets out to become a real-life superhero. His amateur crime-fighting exploits make him a media sensation, but he is soon in over his head as he encounters a sadistic gangster and a father-daughter vigilante team with a far more lethal approach to cleaning up the streets. Comic-book action comedy, with Aaron Taylor-Johnson, Chloe Grace Moretz and Nicolas Cage.

programme.title: Independence Daysaster
programme.desc: America's fourth of July celebrations are abruptly interrupted when Earth is invaded by hostile aliens. Sci-fi thriller, starring Ryan Merriman and Tom Everett Scott.

programme.title: The Last Sharknado: It's About Time

programme.title: The Conjuring
programme.desc: In 1970, paranormal investigators and demonologists Lorraine (Vera Farmiga) and Ed (Patrick Wilson) Warren are summoned to the home of Carolyn (Lili Taylor) and Roger (Ron Livingston) Perron. The Perrons and their five daughters have recently moved into a secluded farmhouse, where a supernatural presence has made itself known. Though the manifestations are relatively benign at first, events soon escalate in horrifying fashion, especially after the Warrens discover the house's macabre history.

programme.title: The Exorcist
programme.desc: One of the most profitable horror movies ever made, this tale of an exorcism is based loosely on actual events. When young Regan (Linda Blair) starts acting odd -- levitating, speaking in tongues -- her worried mother (Ellen Burstyn) seeks medical help, only to hit a dead end. A local priest (Jason Miller), however, thinks the girl may be seized by the devil. The priest makes a request to perform an exorcism, and the church sends in an expert (Max von Sydow) to help with the difficult job.

programme.title: The Shining
programme.desc: Jack Torrance (Jack Nicholson) becomes winter caretaker at the isolated Overlook Hotel in Colorado, hoping to cure his writer's block. He settles in along with his wife, Wendy (Shelley Duvall), and his son, Danny (Danny Lloyd), who is plagued by psychic premonitions. As Jack's writing goes nowhere and Danny's visions become more disturbing, Jack discovers the hotel's dark secrets and begins to unravel into a homicidal maniac hell-bent on terrorizing his family.
